The paper involves computer vision techniques for reading digital data embedded in 3D printed surfaces, which suggests that it could belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) also supports this categorization. Additionally, the paper involves image processing and statistical operations, which could also place it in the Graphics (cs.GR) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The retrieval of watermarks from 3D printed objects could also involve aspects of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR), making these sub-categories possible as well.
